    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-07-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-07-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="1811"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1811">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 319.1123L25/10.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 163.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-07-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 23, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your No. 552, of the
                    9th instant, in which you report that you vigorously protested against the
                    release of the Panaman policeman who is charged with the murder of Corporal
                    Langdon and the shooting of Private Deloughery during the riot in Colon on April
                    2 last.</p>
                <p>The Department approves your action in the matter.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
